ar, as a reminder that even when our nation shines brightest, we are still capable of terrifying things. The illegal interment of American citizens based solely on their race was not the worse thing the US did during world war 2. And it is far from the worst thing that we have done in our history. We should be proud of our accomplishments, defeating the NAZIs and Nationalist in Japan is a great and worthy deed. Insisting that the European powers dismantle their colonial empire post war is a frequently forgotten accomplishment. But we must also be humble and remember the lesson that we are capable of terrible things. Some will try to justify terribleness as necessary, as a mercy to bring wars to swift conclusion. But a simple review will show that the interment of American citizens and the firebombings of civilians did nothing to bring the war to a close. Those things took resources away from the war effort. Remember that democracy is a constant struggle, one that we put ourselves in because we claim the responsibility of governing ourselves. VOTE.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/iRNnQEg</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[sevenfingerman]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>In some companies you have to fight to be appreciated!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/BDBHqlc</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/YUw802m.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/BDBHqlc</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[DumpingSh1tandBeingKind2]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Construction tip</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/k6Wwo2w</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/l4n1ZSH.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/k6Wwo2w</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[DCA4242]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>A Roman street and pedestrian crossing in Pompeii. The lar